ygData.subject: RE: [EQ-Quest] OT: ROK Digest Number 87
ygData.msgSnippet: hehe, please don t get your hopes up, the letter is no guarantee. I hope you do get it but..... A friend of mine has had the confirmation for almost a week
ygData.messageBody:
hehe, please don't get your hopes up, the letter is no guarantee. I hope you
do get it but.....
A friend of mine has had the confirmation for almost a week now, ROK is
still not here. In fact it will be a full week tomorrow since the
confirmation. But we have had Easter break, so maybe that's why :)
But we're in Europe so I'll just buy mine on Friday from the shops which
apparently (So I've been told) have them in stock NOW, but aren't releasing
them to the public till Friday or Saturday.

Ho hum, If this proves to be the case, it would have been quicker to buy it
from the shops than from verant, that doesn't surprise me for some reason,
ah well thankfully the pound is strong at the moment so with no shipping to
pay I'll be getting it at half price ;)
(A cloud with a cp lining I think)

An Ishkar monk (0 level) coming to a ssserver near you ^_^

-----Original Message-----
From: Curtis Bennett [mailto:die_kluge@...]
Sent: 26 April 2000 16:36
To: EQ-Quest@egroups.com
Subject: Re: [EQ-Quest] Digest Number 87


I got my confirmation letter. I expect I should get it today. I was
hoping I could get to level 34 (superior healing!!) before I went, but
I've still got 2 bars to go to get to 33. But apparently there are a
lot of good places to hunt there, so I don't know. I'll probably at
least make an iksar just to check out the city and see what it looks
like. Of course, I still haven't seen Oggok or Paineel, either.
